Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA) Acting Director-General, Calistus Obi was on Monday sentenced to seven years imprisonment by the Federal High Court sitting in Lagos. He was however given an option of N42 million fine by the court. Recall that Justice Mojisola Olatoregun had on May 23 found him guilty of money laundering and converting the agency’s funds to personal use. The court refused to order the forfeiture of his seized assets. Details shortly… 